From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yanghan Ye <yyh94306@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 10 May 2026 03:09:19 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: mt76: mt7996: disable decap offload for AP MLO peers

Keep AP MLO peers on the software 802.11 encap/decap path. The mt7996 MLO header translation path can leave bridged return traffic stuck after association even though the control plane completes successfully.

Signed-off-by: Yanghan Ye <yyh94306@gmail.com>
---
 mt7996/main.c | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mt7996/main.c b/mt7996/main.c
index b515bd0..d8f06fd 100644
--- a/mt7996/main.c
+++ b/mt7996/main.c
@@ -2040,6 +2040,16 @@ static void mt7996_sta_set_decap_offload(struct ieee80211_hw *hw,
 	struct ieee80211_link_sta *link_sta;
 	unsigned int link_id;
 
+	/*
+	 * Keep AP MLO peers on the software 802.11 encap/decap path.
+	 * The mt7996 MLO header translation path can leave bridged return
+	 * traffic stuck after association even though the control plane
+	 * completes successfully.
+	 */
+	if (enabled && vif->type == NL80211_IFTYPE_AP &&
+	    ieee80211_vif_is_mld(vif) && sta->mlo)
+		enabled = false;
+
 	mutex_lock(&dev->mt76.mutex);
 
 	for_each_sta_active_link(vif, sta, link_sta, link_id) {
